#: ../../../creating_packages/package_repo.rst:100
msgid "Capturing the remote and commit from git: ``scm`` [EXPERIMENTAL]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../creating_packages/package_repo.rst:102
msgid ""
"You can use the :ref:`scm attribute <scm_attribute>` with the ``url`` and "
"``revision`` field set to ``auto``. When you export the recipe (or when "
"``conan create`` is called) the exported recipe will capture the remote and "
"commit of the local repository:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../creating_packages/package_repo.rst:106
msgid ""
" from conans import ConanFile, CMake, tools\n"
"\n"
" class HelloConan(ConanFile):\n"
"      scm = {\n"
"         \"type\": \"git\",\n"
"         \"subfolder\": \"hello\",\n"
"         \"url\": \"auto\",\n"
"         \"revision\": \"auto\"\n"
"      }\n"
"     ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../creating_packages/package_repo.rst:121
msgid ""
"The ``conanfile.py`` can be commited and pushed to your origin repository, "
"and will keep always the \"auto\" values. But when the file is exported to "
"the conan local cache, the copied recipe in the local cache, will point to "
"the captured remote and commit:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../creating_packages/package_repo.rst:125
msgid ""
" from conans import ConanFile, CMake, tools\n"
"\n"
" class HelloConan(ConanFile):\n"
"      scm = {\n"
"         \"type\": \"git\",\n"
"         \"subfolder\": \"hello\",\n"
"         \"url\": \"https://github.com/memsharded/hello.git\",\n"
"         \"revision\": \"437676e15da7090a1368255097f51b1a470905a0\"\n"
"      }\n"
"     ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../creating_packages/package_repo.rst:140
msgid ""
"So when you :ref:`upload the recipe <uploading_packages>` to a conan remote, "
"the recipe will contain the \"absolute\" url and commit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../creating_packages/package_repo.rst:143
msgid ""
"When you are requiring your ``HelloConan`` the ``conan install`` will "
"retrieve the recipe from the remote and if you build the package, the source "
"code will be fetched from the captured url/commit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../creating_packages/package_repo.rst:149
msgid ""
"While you are in the same computer (same conan cache), even when you have "
"exported the recipe and conan has captured the absolute url and commit, "
"conan will store the local folder where your source code lives. If you build "
"your package locally it will use the local repository (in the local folder) "
"instead of the remote URL, even if the local directory contains uncommited "
"changes. It allows to speed up the development of your packages cloning from "
"a local repository."
msgstr ""
